        Description copied from class: PsiDocumentManager

      • cancelAndRunWhenAllCommitted

        public boolean cancelAndRunWhenAllCommitted(java.lang.Object key,
                                            java.lang.Runnable action)
        Cancel previously registered action and schedules (new) action to be executed when all documents are committed.
        Parameters:
        key - the (unique) id of the action.
        action - The action to be executed after automatic commit. This action will overwrite any action which was registered under this key earlier. The action will be executed in EDT.
        Returns:
        true if action has been run immediately, or false if action was scheduled for execution later.

      • commitDocument

        public void commitDocument(Document doc)
        Description copied from class: PsiDocumentManager
        Updates the PSI tree for the specified document. Before a modified document is committed, accessing its PSI may return elements corresponding to original (unmodified) state of the document.

        For documents with event-system-enabled PSI (FileViewProvider.isEventSystemEnabled()), should be called in UI thread in a write-safe context (see TransactionGuard). For other documents, can be called in background thread with read access. It's the responsibility of the caller to properly synchronize that PSI and ensure no other threads are reading or modifying it concurrently.

        Specified by:
        commitDocument in class PsiDocumentManager
        Parameters:
        doc - the document to commit.

      • performLaterWhenAllCommitted

        public void performLaterWhenAllCommitted(java.lang.Runnable runnable,
                                         ModalityState modalityState)
        Description copied from class: PsiDocumentManager
        Schedule the runnable to be executed on Swing thread when all the documents with event-system-enabled PSI are committed at some later moment in a given modality state. The runnable is guaranteed to be invoked when no write action is running, and not immediately. If the project is disposed before such moment, the runnable is not run.
        Specified by:
        performLaterWhenAllCommitted in class PsiDocumentManager

      • isDocumentBlockedByPsi

        public boolean isDocumentBlockedByPsi(Document doc)
        Description copied from class: PsiDocumentManager
        Checks if the PSI tree corresponding to the specified document has been modified and the changes have not yet been applied to the document. Documents in that state cannot be modified directly, because such changes would conflict with the pending PSI changes. Changes made through PSI are always applied in the end of a write action, and can be applied in the middle of a write action by calling PsiDocumentManager.doPostponedOperationsAndUnblockDocument(com.intellij.openapi.editor.Document).
        Specified by:
        isDocumentBlockedByPsi in class PsiDocumentManager
        Parameters:
        doc - the document to check.
        Returns:
        true if the corresponding PSI has changes that haven't been applied to the document.

      • getLastCommittedDocument

        public Document getLastCommittedDocument(PsiFile file)
        Description copied from class: PsiDocumentManager
        Returns the document for specified PsiFile intended to be used when working with committed PSI, e.g. outside dispatch thread.
        Specified by:
        getLastCommittedDocument in class PsiDocumentManager
        Parameters:
        file - the file for which the document is requested.
        Returns:
        an immutable document corresponding to the current PSI state. For committed documents, the contents and timestamp are equal to the ones of PsiDocumentManager.getDocument(PsiFile). For uncommitted documents, the text is PsiDocumentManager.getLastCommittedText(Document) and the modification stamp is PsiDocumentManager.getLastCommittedStamp(Document).
